The paper deals with measuring the robustness of neural nets, which is a topic that falls under the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses adversarial attacks and defenses, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for approximating robustness metrics, which could fall under the sub-field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
